{"content":"<header>\n            <small>Getting started<\/small>\n        <h1>Installation<\/h1>\n<\/header><ul class=\"toc\"><li>\n        <a href=\"#new-project\">\n            <span class=\"title\">New project<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n                    <ul class=\"sub-menu\">\n                <li>\n        <a href=\"#1-create-project\">\n            <span class=\"title\">1. Create project<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#2-configure\">\n            <span class=\"title\">2. Configure<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#3-serve\">\n            <span class=\"title\">3. Serve<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#existing-project\">\n            <span class=\"title\">Existing project<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n                    <ul class=\"sub-menu\">\n                <li>\n        <a href=\"#1-add-to-composer\">\n            <span class=\"title\">1. Add to composer<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#2-add-service-provider\">\n            <span class=\"title\">2. Add service provider<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#3-publish-and-configure-the-configuration-file\">\n            <span class=\"title\">3. Publish and configure the configuration file<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#4-publish-the-asset-files\">\n            <span class=\"title\">4. Publish the asset files<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#5-publish-the-view-files-optional\">\n            <span class=\"title\">5. Publish the view files (optional)<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#6-add-composer-codepost-install-cmdcode-to-auto-hook-to-re-publish\">\n            <span class=\"title\">6. Add composer &lt;code&gt;post-install-cmd&lt;\/code&gt; to auto hook to re-publish<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n    <li>\n        <a href=\"#7-configure-codex\">\n            <span class=\"title\">7. Configure Codex<\/span>\n        <\/a>\n            <\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n            <\/li>\n<\/ul><phpdoc-content project=\"codex\" revision=\"master\">\n<p><a name=\"new-project\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h2>New project<\/h2>\n<p>These steps should be followed if you want to install Codex using a new Laravel project. \nIf you are planning on integrating Codex into a existing Laravel project then head over to <a href=\"#existing-project\">Existing Project<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><a name=\"1-create-project\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>1. Create project<\/h4>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"bash\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>composer create-project codex\/codex\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"2-configure\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>2. Configure<\/h4>\n<p>You should now configure Codex to suit your needs. Head over to the <router-link to=\"\/documentation\/codex\/master\/getting-started\/installation\/configuration\" href=\"configuration.md\">configuration<\/router-link> page.<\/p>\n<p><a name=\"3-serve\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>3. Serve<\/h4>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"bash\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>php artisan serve\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"existing-project\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h2>Existing project<\/h2>\n<p>These steps should be followed if you are planning to integrate Codex into a existing Laravel project.<\/p>\n<p><a name=\"1-add-to-composer\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>1. Add to composer<\/h4>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"bash\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>composer require codex\/core\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"2-add-service-provider\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>2. Add service provider<\/h4>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"php\" with-line-numbers with-command-line># config\/app.php\nreturn [\n    \/\/ ...\n    'providers' =&gt; [\n        \/\/ ...\n        Codex\\CodexServiceProvider::class\n    ]\n];\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"3-publish-and-configure-the-configuration-file\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>3. Publish and configure the configuration file<\/h4>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"bash\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>php artisan vendor:publish --provider=Codex\\Core\\CodexServiceProvider --tag=config\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"4-publish-the-asset-files\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>4. Publish the asset files<\/h4>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"bash\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>php artisan vendor:publish --provider=Codex\\Core\\CodexServiceProvider --tag=public\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"5-publish-the-view-files-optional\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>5. Publish the view files (optional)<\/h4>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"bash\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>php artisan vendor:publish --provider=Codex\\Core\\CodexServiceProvider --tag=views\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"6-add-composer-codepost-install-cmdcode-to-auto-hook-to-re-publish\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>6. Add composer <code>post-install-cmd<\/code> to auto hook to re-publish<\/h4>\n<c-code-highlight language=\"json\" with-line-numbers with-command-line>{ \n    \"scripts\": {\n        \"post-install-cmd\": [\n            \"Illuminate\\\\Foundation\\\\ComposerScripts::postInstall\",\n            \"php artisan optimize\",\n            \"php artisan vendor:publish --tag=public --force\"\n        ],\n        \"post-update-cmd\": [\n            \"Illuminate\\\\Foundation\\\\ComposerScripts::postUpdate\",\n            \"php artisan vendor:publish --tag=public --force\"\n        ]\n    }\n}\n<\/c-code-highlight><p><a name=\"7-configure-codex\" class=\"toc-header-link\"><\/a><\/p><h4>7. Configure Codex<\/h4>\n<p>You should now configure Codex to suit your needs. Head over to the <router-link to=\"\/documentation\/codex\/master\/getting-started\/installation\/configuration\" href=\"configuration.md\">configuration<\/router-link> page.<\/p>\n<\/phpdoc-content>","layout":{"header":{"class":{"c-header":true},"style":[],"title":"Codex","revealOnScroll":true,"showTitle":true,"showLeftToggle":true,"showRightToggle":false,"color":"blue-grey-9","menu":[{"_id":"37738fbe-0979-489a-9654-c3cae565d4a8","to":{"name":"phpdoc","params":{"project":"codex","revision":"master"}},"type":"router-link","label":"API","sublabel":"Documentation","icon":"fa-file-code-o","color":"secondary"},{"_id":"e8b0296e-8059-42f9-ad53-bbbfb6a16747","type":"side-menu","side":"right","children":[{"_id":"5a20180b-dfb2-4830-c4f5-8033a96521ac","type":"header","label":"Projects"},{"_id":"4ffde9b3-9678-4213-d9fc-7d0ac24338fe","type":"divider"},{"_id":"1c40d483-9c26-4673-83bc-cffcc8d1459f","type":"router-link","label":"Test Project","sublabel":"This is a testing project","icon":"fa-book","project":"test-zip-project"},{"_id":"cd5bb863-a9ec-48fc-d016-4f13ac2b07e4","type":"router-link","label":"Blade Extensions","sublabel":"Usefull Laravel 5 Blade Directives","icon":"fa-book","project":"blade-extensions"},{"_id":"caa4caf9-5e3c-488c-f7e5-5ef4ce298a60","type":"router-link","label":"Codex","sublabel":"Codex is a file-based documentation system build with Laravel 5.5","icon":"fa-book","project":"codex"},{"_id":"267f9828-798a-490e-922c-b670a43ea97c","type":"router-link","label":"General Documentation","sublabel":"General documentation for personal reference covering a wide array of subjects","icon":"fa-book","project":"general"}],"label":"Codex","sublabel":"Project","icon":"fa-book"},{"_id":"33b7edfe-66ab-4b76-c780-16564e42f14b","type":"side-menu","side":"right","children":[{"_id":"e01ed0e9-28c8-413d-de84-e52d0c7012f3","type":"header","label":"Revisions"},{"_id":"8bc3a722-c4d5-48b5-bba3-948a26b1ce1c","type":"divider"},{"_id":"226fef21-718d-487f-bb9c-5eb7565ebe06","type":"router-link","label":"2.0.0-alpha","icon":"